{"key":"processedPost-17771371","value":{"id":17771371,"first":17770878,"last":17772594,"when":1360413881,"utime":"02/09/13 02:44 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /> Colonizes extremely fast, produces huge yield and is strong against contamination. </blockquote><br />Apparently you haven't used any other grain yet if you feel this way.&nbsp; Popcorn does not colonize fast.&nbsp; The kernels are huge, so a jar of popcorn has less than half the mycelium of a jar of rye, oats, millet, etc.&nbsp; Thus when a 'jar' colonizes a few days faster but has only half the mycelium, it's actually slower.<br />Popcorn does not increase yield over other grains.&nbsp; It is the <i>most prone</i> to contamination of all the grains, probably again due to the large kernel size which leads to insufficient sterilization.&nbsp; Use it as a last resort if nothing else is available, but certainly not as a grain of choice where reliable spawn media is available.<br />RR","title":"Re: Popcorn tek is the easiest"}}